basin. Cover with a buttered circle of greaseproof paper, with a pleat in the middle to allow for pudding to expand. Cover with lid or secure with a circle of foil, again with a pleat in the middle. Secure with string then place in Varoma dish."},{"content":"Place 1400 g boiling water in mixing bowl. Place covered Varoma into position and steam <b>90 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Add remaining 900 g boiling water before steaming again <b>60-70 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Set covered Varoma aside for 10 minutes while making sauce."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Chocolate Sauce"},{"content":"Place chocolate, cream and water in mixing bowl then melt <b>3 min\/60째C\/speed 2<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and melt again <b>2 min\/60째C\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Remove lid or foil and greaseproof paper from pudding basin then turn out onto a serving plate. Serve warm with chocolate sauce poured over."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Instead of the more traditional fruit laden Christmas pudding, this steamed chocolate dessert provides an alternative ending to a Christmas Day meal. Bursting with the flavours of zesty orange and rich chocolate, this pudding can be left to steam gently in the Varoma while the turkey is roasting in the oven."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","3h","8 portions"]}